wdi2-SL.FAM.WORK.FE.ZS.def: Contributing family workers are those workers who hold "self-employment jobs" as own-account workers in a market-oriented establishment operated by a related person living in the same household.
wdi2-SL.FAM.WORK.FE.ZS.name: Contributing family workers
wdi2-SL.FAM.WORK.FE.ZS.source: International Labour Organization, ILOSTAT database. Data retrieved on January 29, 2021.
